{"lemma":"خَلْقُ","slug":"خَلْقُ","root":"خ.ل.ق","root_slug":"خ-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَلْق","root":"خلق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":52},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":9,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":26},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11381","n11386","n11387","n11388","n11389","n11390","n11407"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to create, to make","examples":[{"text":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلنَّاسُ ٱعْبُدُوا۟ رَبَّكُمُ ٱلَّذِى خَلَقَكُمْ وَٱلَّذِينَ مِن قَبْلِكُمْ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَتَّقُونَ","english":"O mankind, worship your Lord, who created you and those before you, that you may become righteous -"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape, to form"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be suitable, be fit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perfume"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلَقَ (ḵalaqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creation","examples":[{"text":"لِخَلْقِ بِيئَةٍ جَيِّدَةٍ، يَجِبُ أَنّ تُهَوِّيَ حَوْضَ السَّمَكِ بِٱنْتِظَامٍ.","english":"To create a good environment, you must aerate the fish tank regularly."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creation (“all which exists”), creatures","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"people","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"أَنَامُ مِلْءَ جُفُونِي عَنْ شَوارِدِهَا / وَيَسْهَرُ الْخَلْقُ جَرَّاهَا وَيَخْتَصِمُ","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pleb, plebeian"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"natural disposition, character, nature"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inborn quality"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manners, character"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"morals, morality","examples":[{"text":"Ahmad Shawqi\nوَإِنَّمَا ٱلْأُمَمُ ٱلْأَخْلَاقُ مَا بَقِيَتْ / فَإِنْ هُمُ ذَهَبَتْ أَخْلَاقُهُمْ ذَهَبُوا\nwaʔinnamā l-ʔumamu l-ʔaḵlāqu mā baqiyat / faʔin humu ḏahabat ʔaḵlāquhum ḏahabū","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anger, irritation","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bravery","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religion","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"humanity","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"refinement","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of خِلْقَة (ḵilqa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be old and worn out (of a garment)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smooth and soft (of an item, through wear)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلِقَ (ḵaliqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rags"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old age"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"men, people"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"worn, threadbare"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *ḫalaq-, cognate with Biblical Hebrew חָלַק (ḥɔláq, ḥālaq, “to divide”), Classical Syriac ܚܠܩ (ḥəlaq, “to divide, apportion”), Sabaean [script needed] (ḫlq, “compensation, portion, lot”), and Minaean [script needed] (ḫlq). Took on the senses of creation and formation prior to the advent of Islam, as indicated by passages like Qur'an (in Arabic), 609–632 CE, 39:38, where the term is already understood by non-Muslim interlocutors, likely influenced by ancient Near Eastern mythology, in which the world was created by dividing pre-existing matter.\n\nProbably denominal from the perfume compound خَلُوق (ḵalūq), خِلَاق (ḵilāq), which is then from the base stem “to create, to compose” above.\n\nPlausibly a liquid variant of خ ر ق (ḵ r q), but it is sensible that it rather relates to Biblical Hebrew חָלַק (ḥɔláq, “to be smooth, slippery”) and Akkadian 𒄩𒀀 (ḫalāqum, “to vanish”)."},"ipa":["/xa.la.qa/","/xa.lu.qa/","/xal.la.qa/","/xalq/","/xu.luq/","/xi.laq/","/xa.li.qa/","/xa.laq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11381","headword_ar":"خَلْقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measuring;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"determining the measure, proportion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by measure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to the measure of another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportioning"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqodiyrN","text_ar":"تَقْدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K, TA, and Bd in ii. 19:) this is the primary meaning. (Msb, TA, and Bd ubi suprà.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa AlA^adiymi","text_ar":"خَلَقَ الاَدِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqapN","text_ar":"خَلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He measured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qad~ara","text_ar":"قَدَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hide, and sewed it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he measured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qd~r","text_ar":"قدّر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"limaA yuriydu","text_ar":"لِمَا يُرِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, that which he desired"},{"kind":"text","text":"to make of it], (JK, * TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lils~iqaA='i","text_ar":"لِلسِّقَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, the skin for water or milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"that he desired to make], (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before cutting it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he measured it"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAsahu","text_ar":"قَاسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to cut from it a water-bag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a water-skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a boot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa Aln~iTaEa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ النِّطَعَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he measured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nTE","text_ar":"نطع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: when one cuts it, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAhu","text_ar":"فَرَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa Aln~aEola","text_ar":"خَلَقَ النَّعْلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He determined the measure of the sandal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportioned it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qad~arahaA","text_ar":"قَدَّرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it by measure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd in ii. 19.) Hence the saying of Zuheyr, (S,) praising Herim Ibn-Sinán, (TA,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":800},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaA^anota taforiY maA xalaqota wabaEo\n                      \n                     \n                        Du Alqawomi yaxoluqu vum~a laA yaforiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"In the preceding quotation, the final character of the first line and initial character of the second are missing in the original text."},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And thou indeed cuttest what thou hast measured; but some of the people measure, then will not cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) i. e., when thou determinest upon a thing thou executest it; but others determine upon that which they do not execute. (TA.) And El-Hajjáj said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA xalaqotu A_il~aA qarayotu waEadotu","text_ar":"مَا خَلَقْتُ اـِلَّا قَرَيْتُ وَعَدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA wafayotu","text_ar":"اـِلَّا وَفَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not measured unless I have"},{"kind":"text","text":"afterwards"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut, and I have not promised unless I have"},{"kind":"text","text":"afterwards"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoluqu lakumo","text_ar":"اَخْلُقُ لَكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlT~iyni kahayoy^api AlT~ayori","text_ar":"مِنَ الطِّينِ كَهَيْيَةِ الطَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur iii. 43, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will form for you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will make according to its proper measure"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uqad~iru","text_ar":"اُقَدِّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for you,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of clay, a thing like the form of the bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of birds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd, Jel.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] it signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into existence according to a certain measure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportion, and so as to make it equal"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ksh and Bd in ii. 19:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"producing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after a pattern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"model, which one has devised, not after the similitude of anything preexisting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is another meaning which it has in the [classical] language of the Arabs. (TA.) As the act of God, it signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing into being"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"anything,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not after the similitude of anything pre-existing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creating"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing; and thus it is generally best rendered; as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing into existence from a state of non-existence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa A@ll~`hu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"خَلَقَ ا@للّٰهُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God brought the thing into existence"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after it had not been:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the act of God, signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"creating out of nothing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uEobuduwA rab~akumu A@l~a*iY xalaqakumo","text_ar":"اُعْبُدُوا رَبَّكُمُ ا@لَّذِى خَلَقَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur ii. 19, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Serve ye your Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who brought you into existence when ye were nothing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel. [But in other passages of the Kur (vi. 2 &c.) it is said that God created ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") mankind of clay.]) Accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa A@ll~`hu Alxaloqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ ا@للّٰهُ الخَلْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tropical phrase, meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God brought into existence the creation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"created beings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind, according to a predetermination"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqodiyr","text_ar":"تَقْدِير"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"required by wisdom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi xaliyqatuhu Al~atiY xuliqa EalayohaA","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ خَلِيقَتُهُ الَّتِى خُلِقَ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuliqahaA","text_ar":"خُلِقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~atiY xuliqa","text_ar":"الَّتِى خُلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluqN","text_ar":"خُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fabricated"},{"kind":"text","text":"speech, or a saying or sentence, &c.: (K, * TA:) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he forged"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA) a saying, (Msb,) or a lie, or a falsehood; (S, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axtlq","text_ar":"اختلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txl~q","text_ar":"تخلّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~avanaA","text_ar":"حَدَّثَنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN biA^aHaAdiyvi Alxaloqi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بِاَحَادِيثِ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one related to us fictitious tales"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stories, such as are deemed pretty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are told by night"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for entertainment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in the Kur [xxvi. 137], accord. to one reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino h`*aA A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِنْ هٰذَا اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqu AlA^aw~aliyna","text_ar":"خَلْقُ الاَوَّلِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is nought but the lying, and forging, of the ancients."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in the same [xxxviii. 6], ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino h`*aA A_il~aA A@xotilaAqN","text_ar":"اـِنْ هٰذَا اـِلَّا ا@خْتِلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is nought but forging, and lying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqahu","text_ar":"خَلَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it smooth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xl~qhu","text_ar":"خلّقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; namely, an arrow, (S,) [and any other thing; for] of anything that has been made smooth one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xul~iqa","text_ar":"خُلِّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it equable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, wood, or a stick; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xl~qhu","text_ar":"خلّقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoliyqN","text_ar":"تَخْلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqato","text_ar":"خَلُقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAqapN","text_ar":"خَلَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a woman, (JK, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She had"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a goodly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body and make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, goodly in make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well made."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [In the CK, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna xaloquhaA","text_ar":"حَسُنَ خَلْقُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", is put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna xuluquhA","text_ar":"حَسُنَ خُلُقُها"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, good in nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqa","text_ar":"خَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqN","text_ar":"خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, S; *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa","text_ar":"خَلُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwqapN","text_ar":"خُلُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAqapN","text_ar":"خَلَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqapN","text_ar":"خُلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v. infrà];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, smooth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 12. And it seems that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqati AlS~axorapu","text_ar":"خَلِقَتِ الصَّخْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqN","text_ar":"خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rock was free from crack or fracture."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa","text_ar":"خَلُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqa","text_ar":"خَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) inf. n. (of the first, JK, S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwqapN","text_ar":"خُلُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAqapN","text_ar":"خَلَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA) and [of the second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqN","text_ar":"خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of the third]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluwqN","text_ar":"خُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a garment)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, old, and worn out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axlq","text_ar":"اخلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixolaAqN","text_ar":"اـِخْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axlwlq","text_ar":"اخلولق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAjuhu","text_ar":"دِيبَاجُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axlq","text_ar":"اخلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face became worn out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became used for mean service"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it lost its grace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was disgraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] by his begging. (Har p. 476. [See also 4 below.]) [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAbahu","text_ar":"شَبَابَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axlq","text_ar":"اخلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His youth declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa","text_ar":"خَلُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalAqapN","text_ar":"خَلاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ham p. 522,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyq","text_ar":"خَلِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiyr","text_ar":"جَدِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adapted"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed by nature, apt, meet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqN","text_ar":"خَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below]. (S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa l*`lika","text_ar":"خَلُقَ لذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi*`lika","text_ar":"بِذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqN","text_ar":"خَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, adapted, disposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though he were one of those in whom that was reckoned to be, and in whom the symptoms, signs, or tokens, thereof were seen. (S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa A^ano yafoEala *`lika","text_ar":"خَلُقَ اَنْ يَفْعَلَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^ano yfEl *lk","text_ar":"بِاَنْ يفعل ذلك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^ano yfEl *lk","text_ar":"لِاَنْ يفعل ذلك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^ano","text_ar":"مَنْ اَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yfEl *lk","text_ar":"يفعل ذلك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, adapted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqN","text_ar":"خَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluqa","text_ar":"خَلُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may signify also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, probable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"likely to happen"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to have happened"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"been:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqN","text_ar":"خَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","JK","Jel","Ksh","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n11386","headword_ar":"خَلْقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa","text_ar":"خَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, S, Msb, K, &c.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN taAm~u Alxaloqi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ تَامُّ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man complete,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfect, in respect of make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, K. * [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloqapN","text_ar":"خِلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [In this and similar instances,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloq","text_ar":"الخَلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fashion of the outer man, and its"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities and attributes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxuluqu","text_ar":"الخُلُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ the fashion of the inner man, ” &c. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqu","text_ar":"الخَلْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in the sense of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaxoluwqu","text_ar":"المَخْلُوقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is created; the creature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA, and Bd in xxiii. 17, &c.:) [and, collectively,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the creation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, that are created;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all created things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ubi suprà, &c.:) and [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxliyqapu","text_ar":"الخلِيقَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, * K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind and the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii, and others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in lv. 9, &c.:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxliyqapu","text_ar":"الخلِيقَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [its pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAy^iqu","text_ar":"خَلَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo xaliyqapu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هُمْ خَلِيقَةُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo xalqu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هُمْ خَلقُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the creatures of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqu","text_ar":"الخَلْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being originally an inf. n.: (S, TA:) and Lh mentions [an instance of its having a pl., in] the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA waA@l~a*iY xalaqa Alxuluwqa maA faEalotu ka*aA","text_ar":"لَا وَا@لَّذِى خَلَقَ الخُلُوقَ مَا فَعَلْتُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, by Him who created"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all creatures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falayugay~irun~a xaloqa A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"فَلَيُغَيِّرُنَّ خَلْقَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [iv. 118, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they shall alter the creature of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"], some say that castration is meant: (TA: [and Bd includes, with this, other unnatural actions:]) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the religion of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel, TA;) accord. to El-Hasan and Mujáhid. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tabodiyla lixaloqi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"لَا تَبْدِيلَ لِخَلْقِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxx. 29], means, accord. to Katádeh, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no changing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the religion of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made smooth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxal~aqN","text_ar":"مُخَلَّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n11387","headword_ar":"خُلْقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluqN","text_ar":"خُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11388","headword_ar":"خَلَقُ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqa","text_ar":"خَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as such, signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being smooth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]. (JK, S. *) [As such also,] in a rock,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Freedom from crack or fracture."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  [And, as such,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being old, and worn out."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, used as an epithet,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old, and worn out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) [and as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and worn-out garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqaAnN","text_ar":"خُلْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAqN","text_ar":"اَخْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * K, * TA.) And [as an epithet] it is masc. and fem.; (S, K;) because it is originally an inf. n., the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaqu","text_ar":"اَخْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ smooth, ” (S,) [or rather of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqa","text_ar":"خَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ it was, or became, old, and worn out; ” although it has pls.; and] IB mentions an instance of its dual,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqaAni","text_ar":"خَلَقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) Ks says, We have not heard them say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqapN","text_ar":"خَلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any instance: (Lh, TA:) Fr says that it is without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as a fem. epithet] because it was originally used as a prefixed noun; for one said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTiniY","text_ar":"اَعْطِنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa jub~atika","text_ar":"خَلَقَ جُبَّتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqa EimaAmatika","text_ar":"خَلَقَ عِمَامَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou to me what is old, and worn out, of thy"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jb~p","text_ar":"جبّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of thy turban"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but Ez-Zejjájee says that this is nought. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN xalaqN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old and worn-out garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHafapN xalaqN","text_ar":"مِلْحَفَةٌ خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and worn-out outer wrapping garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rum~apN xalaqN","text_ar":"رُمَّةٌ خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and worn-out piece of rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN xalaqN","text_ar":"دَارٌ خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and decayed house"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jisomN xalaqN","text_ar":"جِسْمٌ خَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and wasted body"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAqN","text_ar":"اَخْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, altogether,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wholly, old and worn out;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, K;) every portion of it being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaq","text_ar":"خَلَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr;) like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buromapN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"بُرْمَةٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (S:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaA='apN A^axolaAqN","text_ar":"مُلَا=ءَةٌ اَخْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar.) And Ks mentions the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaHato viyaAbuhumo xuloqaAnFA wa xalaquhumo jududFA","text_ar":"اَصْبَحَتْ ثِيَابُهُمْ خُلْقَانًا وَ خَلَقُهُمْ جُدُدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their garments became old, and worn out; and their old and worn-out garments"},{"kind":"text","text":"became replaced by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; with the sing. [in the latter clause] in the place of the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqaAn","text_ar":"خُلْقَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jududFA","text_ar":"جُدُدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be here put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydFA","text_ar":"جَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd","text_ar":"جد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) In the phrase ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHafapN xulayoqN","text_ar":"مِلْحَفَةٌ خُلَيْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An outer wrapping garment that is a little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat, old, and worn out"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the dim. is without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is [the dim. of] an epithet [applied without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a fem. n.], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not affixed to the dims. of epithets [of this kind]: it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSayufN","text_ar":"نُصَيُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSafN","text_ar":"نَصَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"an epithet applied to a woman. (S, K. * [See Lumsden's Arab. Gram. p. 623: but some of the grammarians consider these instances as anomalous.]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEahu biyEapa Alxalaqi","text_ar":"بَاعَهُ بِيعَةَ الخَلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoEa *iY Alxalaqi","text_ar":"بَيْعَ ذِى الخَلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter as used by a poet, [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bought it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sold it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(app. the former,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as one buys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sells, the old and worn-out garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as we say “ dogcheap, ” and “ cheap as dirt ”], are phrases mentioned, but not explained, by IAar, who cites the following saying:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aboligo fazaArapa A^an~iY qado $arayotu lahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        majoda AlHayaApi bisayofiY bayoEa *iY Alxalaqi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tell thou Fezárah that I have purchased for them life-long glory"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the glory of life"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with my sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as cheaply, i. e as easily,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as one purchases the old and worn-out garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbapN xalaqapN","text_ar":"سَحَابَةٌ خَلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n11389","headword_ar":"خَلِقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqa","text_ar":"خَلِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sHaAbapN","text_ar":"سحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliqapN","text_ar":"خَلِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cloud in which is a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trace, of rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqapN","text_ar":"خَلِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cloud giving hope of rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqaA='u","text_ar":"خَلْقَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK;) both are said by IAar to signify the same: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqapN","text_ar":"خَلَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone, as a subst., or probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbapN","text_ar":"سَحَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaqapN","text_ar":"خَلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cloud that is equable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform, giving hope of rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n11390","headword_ar":"خُلُقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqN","text_ar":"خُلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a natural, a native,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an innate, disposition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temper"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajiy~apN","text_ar":"سَجِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaboEN","text_ar":"طَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which one is created:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiloqapN","text_ar":"خِلْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [the same; i. e.] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiTorapN","text_ar":"فِطْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (S, Msb, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which a man is created;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) like ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluqN","text_ar":"خُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqN","text_ar":"خُلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA: [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloq","text_ar":"خَلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqapN","text_ar":"خَلِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also] signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiyEap","text_ar":"طَبِيعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which a man is created:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the proper signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluqN","text_ar":"خُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moral character;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashion of the inner man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soul, and its peculiar qualities and attributes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaloqN","text_ar":"خَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the “ fashion of the outer man, and its [peculiar] qualities and attributes: ” it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"custom"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a second nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuloqN","text_ar":"خُلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is merely a contraction thereof, and therefore identical with it in all its senses,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manliness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruwo'apN","text_ar":"مُرُوْءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAqN","text_ar":"اَخْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only: (TA:) [this is often used as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ethics:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyqapN","text_ar":"خَلِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense explained above [said in Har p. 193 to be that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuluqN","text_ar":"خُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaAy^iqN","text_ar":"خَلَايِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa $aYo'N fiY AlmiyzaAni A^avoqala mino Husoni Alxuluqi","text_ar":"لَيْسَ شَىْءٌ فِى المِيزَانِ اَثْقَلَ مِنْ حُسْنِ الخُلُقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing is heavier in the balance"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which good and evil will be weighed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than goodness of the moral character,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayohaA","text_ar":"عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~atiY xuliqa","text_ar":"الَّتِى خُلِقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi xaliyqatuhu","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ خَلِيقَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuliqahaA","text_ar":"خُلِقَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~atiY xuliqa","text_ar":"الَّتِى خُلِقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is his nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which he was created."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lakariymu Alxaliyqapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَكَرِيمُ الخَلِيقَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is generous in respect of nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (AZ.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra *`lika lahu xuluqFA","text_ar":"صَارَ ذٰلِكَ لَهُ خُلُقًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That became to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a second nature, a habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing to which he was habituated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in the Kur [xxvi. 137],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino h`*aA A_il~aA xuluqu AlA^aw~aliyna","text_ar":"اـِنْ هٰذَا اـِلَّا خُلُقُ الاَوَّلِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is nought but a custom of the ancients."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in the same [lxviii. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A_in~aka laEalaY xuluqK EaZiymK","text_ar":"وَ اـِنَّكَ لَعَلَى خُلُقٍ عَظِيمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily thou art of a great religion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, TA.) And in a trad. of 'Áïsheh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna xuluquhu AlqaroA=na","text_ar":"كَانَ خُلُقُهُ القَرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That whereto he clung was the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with its rules of discipline and its command and its prohibitions, and the excellences and beauties and gracious things comprised in it. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawomapu Alxulqi","text_ar":"نَوْمَةُ الخُلقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxuluqi","text_ar":"الخُلُقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxuloqi","text_ar":"الخُلْقِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sleep of midday,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which was prescribed by the Prophet. (Har p. 223. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumoqN","text_ar":"حُمْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuroqN","text_ar":"خُرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n11407","headword_ar":"خُلَّقٌ","root":"xlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaqu","text_ar":"اَخْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}